*************** APPLICABILITY ***************
The below mentioned upgrade steps are applicable to you if you are upgrading from a release version <= v1.0.2 
These changes are recommended to the sync database for better compatibility with future releases.

*************** WARNING ***************
1. DO NOT perform any/all of the steps mentioned below before creating a reliable backup of the database. Check Backup section of Data management page in the Wiki for more details.
2. Make sure the application is offline before performing the below mentioned steps to avoid unpredictable changes to the data/database.

*************** UPGRADE STEPS ***************
Perform the steps mentioned below depending upon to the database product you are using to complete upgrade of your application.


#### MariaDB / Mysql

# Execute below SQL statements to alter required table(s).
ALTER TABLE cards_addressbook MODIFY COLUMN user_specific CHAR(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1', MODIFY COLUMN writable CHAR(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1';
ALTER TABLE propertystorage MODIFY COLUMN path TEXT NOT NULL, MODIFY COLUMN name TEXT NOT NULL, MODIFY COLUMN valuetype INTEGER;

# Execute SQL statements present in below mentioned files(s) from this release.
sql/mysql/30_trigger_ddl.sql


#### PostgreSQL

# Execute below SQL statements to alter required table(s).
ALTER TABLE cards_addressbook ALTER COLUMN user_specific TYPE CHAR(1) USING (user_specific::INTEGER), ALTER COLUMN user_specific SET DEFAULT '1', ALTER COLUMN writable TYPE CHAR(1) USING (writable::INTEGER), ALTER COLUMN writable SET DEFAULT '1';
ALTER TABLE propertystorage ALTER COLUMN path TYPE TEXT, ALTER COLUMN name TYPE TEXT, ALTER COLUMN valuetype TYPE INTEGER;

# Execute SQL statements present in below mentioned files(s) from this release.
sql/pgsql/30_trigger_ddl.sql


#### SQLite

# Create target database as per "-- Sync database creation" section in the INSTALL file.
# Follow the data migration process defined in DATA_MIGRATION file to upgrade.
